## `test_chunk_size_preserved_across_reopen(tmp_db)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-dura-9 -->

### Purpose
Chunk size is pinned at mkfs time in the `schema_version` row. Reopening with a different library instance sees the same chunk size — implementations must not assume the default.

### Postconditions

```python
mkfs(str(tmp_db), chunk_size=32768)    # 32 KiB
fs = open_fs(str(tmp_db))
assert fs._chunk_size() == 32768
fs.close()

fs = open_fs(str(tmp_db))
assert fs._chunk_size() == 32768
fs.close()
```

