## `test_synchronous_full(tmp_db)`
<!-- checksum: placeholder-dura-14 -->

### Purpose
`synchronous=FULL` is the durability knob — power loss must not lose committed writes. Verify the DB opens with synchronous=FULL regardless of whether this is the first open or a reopen.

### Postconditions

```python
mkfs(str(tmp_db))

fs = open_fs(str(tmp_db))
# Library exposes a private hook for tests.
assert fs._sqlite_pragma("synchronous") == 2   # FULL
fs.close()

fs = open_fs(str(tmp_db))
assert fs._sqlite_pragma("synchronous") == 2
fs.close()
```

